<refentry id="org.bus1.coredump">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>org.bus1.coredump</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>org.bus1.coredump</refname>
    <refpurpose>Kernel Core Dump Handler</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><command>org.bus1.coredump</command> is executed by the kernel when
    a process aborts abnormally. It extracts a stack trace and writes it to
    the kernel log buffer, and alternatively stores the core dump in the
    <filename>/var/coredump</filename> directory.</para>
  </refsect1>

